Notes:
  - The plan spec asked for the reaper to "emit a browser_session_expired
    activity event into the latest open run for that workspace". That logic
    is in `public.reap_expired_browser_sites()` but was not triggered during
    fixture verify because the operator workspace had no open runs at the
    moment of reap. The path is exercised by the function body for future
    real expirations; live operator-driven coverage will land in E.5 when a
    real workspace_browser_sites row exists with an open run.

  - storage_state_json column is intentionally JSONB and unindexed. It stores
    the Browserbase context blob (cookies + localStorage). API endpoints
    (E.4) must never return this column in responses. The single SELECT RLS
    policy is the only consumer; service_role writes via E.4.
